652}}\n[assistant-event] thinking_start\n[thinking] **Evaluating coroutine initialization issues**\n[thinking] \n[thinking] I’m considering that if the parent `Dispatchers` is already initialized before `coroutinesCoreJar` reads the `codeSource`, there could be complications. There’s also a potential issue with test execution under JUnit when running tests in parallel. If both tests execute at the same time, it seems the first parent `Dispatchers` initializes properly without conflict for the second child. However, since `Dispatchers.Main` initialization is global and includes a service resource provider, I'm noting that it’s all functioning well.\n[thinking] \n[assistant-event] thinking_end\n[tool-call] start id=unknown\n[tool-call] delta {\"path\":\"tests/src/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/kotlinx-coroutines-core-jvm/1.6.4/user-code-filter.json\"}\n[tool-call] end id=call_UFCng9Q4PtIYA4VX4FXXNxxC|fc_0f1c3c54acaf114a0169f8f860ec14819eb8595a9821862a9d name=read args={\"path\": \"tests/src/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/kotlinx-coroutines-core-jvm/1.6.4/user-code-filter.json\"}\n[recv] {\"type\": \"message_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Evaluating coroutine initialization issues**\\n\\nI’m considering that if the parent `Dispatchers` is already initialized before `coroutinesCoreJar` reads the `codeSource`, there could be complications. There’s also a potential issue with test execution under JUnit when running tests in parallel. If both tests execute at the same time, it seems the first parent `Dispatchers` initializes properly without conflict for the second child. However, since `Dispatchers.Main` initialization is global and includes a service resource provider, I'm noting that it’s all functioning well.\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_0f1c3c54acaf114a0169f8f8567d60819ea52ab50c847f7e3d\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABp-PhgiRZndfARWZ52q_xHPavBomhy0aKU_Xkv7eV